Use the `POST` verb to create an Atlas Resource Policy for your organization.
The request must include:* `name`: The name of the Atlas Resource Policy.

* `policies`: The cluster restrictions you defined in [Cedar policy language](https://docs.cedarpolicy.com/) in the previous step. If       you use quotes (`"`) in `policies.body`, escape with a backslash (`\`).Example `POST` request:> **Note:** This `curl` command uses a service account access token ([OAuth 2.0](https://oauth.net/2/)) to authenticate
> instead of API keys. To learn more, see [API Access Lists endpoint](atlas-admin-api-access).```sh
curl --header "Authorization: Bearer {ACCESS-TOKEN}" \
     --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
     --header "Accept: application/vnd.atlas.2024-08-05+json" \
     --include \
     --request POST "https://cloud.mongodb.com/api/atlas/v2/orgs/{ORG-ID}/resourcePolicies?pretty=true" \
     --data '{
       "name": "MyResourcePolicy",
       "policies": [
         {
           "body": "forbid (principal, action == ResourcePolicy::Action::\"cluster.modify\", resource)    when {context.cluster.regions.contains(ResourcePolicy::Region::\"aws:us-west-1\")};"
         }
       ]
     }'
